<h2>Patronal meaning</h2>
<p>The brotherhood bears Peter’s name; on <strong>29 June</strong> (Saints Peter and Paul) it celebrates <strong>solemn Mass</strong> for its apostolic Titular, professing communion with the Church of Rome and Peter’s ministry of unity and forgiveness.</p>
<h2>Liturgy</h2>
<p>Preaching links the apostle to parish life in La Línea; members attend with insignia; the spiritual director guides intercessions. Moderate flowers, choir and incense follow parish norms; optional social or charitable acts may follow.</p>
<h2>Chapter IV</h2>
<p>Alongside Christological and Marian feasts, Art. 22 honours the <strong>apostolic foundation</strong> of the Church. Peter’s intercession is sought for leaders and bishops; the day gives thanks for the parish home of Christ of Mercy and Mary of Health.</p>
